  "prompt": "How can I know that I am not in the friend zone?",
  "response": "Determining if you're not in the friend zone involves observing various social and emotional cues. While there is no definitive way to know, here are some signs that may suggest they see you as more than just a friend:\n\n1. **Physical Affection**: They may initiate physical contact more frequently, such as hugging, touching your arm, or playful interactions.\n\n2. **Quality Time**: They make an effort to spend a lot of time with you one-on-one, rather than in group settings.\n\n3. **Personal Attention**: They show a genuine interest in your life, ask thoughtful questions, and remember details about you.\n\n4. **Compliments**: They give compliments that go beyond platonic praise, possibly hinting at attraction.\n\n5. **Future Plans**: They include you in their future plans or speak about activities you could do together in the long term.\n\n6. **Flirting**: There's clear flirtatious behavior, such as teasing, playful banter, and jokingly flirting.\n\n7. **Jealousy**: They display signs of jealousy when you talk about potential romantic interests.\n\n8. **Communication**: They frequently text or call you, showing excitement to talk or share things about their day.\n\n9. **Body Language**: Positive and open body language, such as leaning in closer, maintaining eye contact, and smiling often.\n\n10. **Confessions**: They may straightforwardly express their feelings or hint that they like you in a romantic way.\n\nEvery person is different, and these signs can vary, but combined, they generally suggest romantic interest. If you\u2019re unsure, having an open conversation about your feelings might be the best way to clarify where you both stand.",
